@page "/carousel"
<PageTitle>Carousel - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1 id="carousel">Carousel</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                The Carousel component creates a slideshow for cycling through content —
                images, cards, or any child elements.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <pre><code>&lt;Carousel&gt;
    &lt;Img Src="slide1.jpg" /&gt;
    &lt;Img Src="slide2.jpg" /&gt;
    &lt;Img Src="slide3.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;/Carousel&gt;</code></pre>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="parameters">Parameters</h2>

            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr><td>Class</td><td>string?</td><td>Additional CSS classes.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Style</td><td>string?</td><td>Inline styles.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>ChildContent</td><td>RenderFragment</td><td>Slide elements.</td></tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="carousel-bootstrap">Bootstrap 5 Carousel</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Bootstrap 5 Carousel</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Bootstrap 5, the Carousel component maps to the Bootstrap carousel class
                with the required data-bs-ride attribute. Slide navigation is handled by
                Bootstrap's JavaScript bundle. Each child element is wrapped in a carousel-item
                div. The Bootstrap 5 design system injects the necessary class names and
                data attributes automatically.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="carousel-daisyui">DaisyUI Carousel</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">DaisyUI Carousel</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In DaisyUI, the Carousel component maps to the DaisyUI carousel class. DaisyUI's
                carousel is CSS-only and uses scroll snapping instead of JavaScript-driven slides.
                Navigation between slides is done via anchor links to slide IDs. The DaisyUI design
                system applies the carousel and carousel-item classes and the snap behavior is
                handled entirely by CSS without any JavaScript dependency.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="carousel-basecoat">Basecoat Carousel</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Basecoat Carousel</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Basecoat, the Carousel component is composed from Tailwind utility classes
                that implement a horizontal scrollable container with scroll snapping. The
                overflow, flex layout, and snap alignment are expressed as Tailwind utilities
                defined in the Basecoat design system. You can adjust the snap behavior and
                scrollbar visibility through the Specialization or Class parameters.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("carousel", "Carousel"),
    new TocItem("overview", "Overview", 2),
    new TocItem("parameters", "Parameters", 2),
    new TocItem("carousel-bootstrap", "Bootstrap 5 Carousel", 2),
    new TocItem("carousel-daisyui", "DaisyUI Carousel", 2),
    new TocItem("carousel-basecoat", "Basecoat Carousel", 2)
])" />

</div>
